Ash is runnable in a linux enviroment with the command ./ash
Ash is able to execute normal unix commands
Ash can change directory with cd
Ash can print history with command history/h, and is able to execute previous commands from history with history {history number} or h {history number}
Can run multiple commands through a pipeline with |
Can run commands in the background by ending command with &
can view commands in background with jobs
can stop commands runnning in foreground with ctr + z
can restart commands in foreground with fg to start the most recent command in the foreground and fg {Job number} to start a specfic job in the foreground
can restart commands in background with bg to start the most recent command in the background and bg {Job number} to start a specfic job in the background
can call kill {Job number} to end a job
